---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../components/SiteNav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import CoverSection from '../components/CoverSection.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import FeatureItem from '../components/FeatureItem.astro';
import ImageSlider from '../components/ImageSlider.astro';
import Tabs from '../components/Tabs.astro';
import MediaImage from '../components/MediaImage.astro';

const cdn = 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/6970bf7914853738a0b435bf/6970bf7b14853738a0b436';

const heroSlides = [
	{ src: `${cdn}8c_post5.webp`, alt: 'Calm waters at dawn' },
	{ src: `${cdn}8f_post3.webp`, alt: 'Sailboat on open water' },
	{ src: `${cdn}90_post2.webp`, alt: 'Harbour at sunset' },
	{ src: `${cdn}8e_post1.webp`, alt: 'Coastal landscape' },
	{ src: `${cdn}8d_post6.webp`, alt: 'Mist over the sea' },
];

const burdenItems = [
	'The fatigue of constantly context-switching between inconsistent approaches.',
	'The frustration of beautiful ideas compromised by clunky execution.',
	'The weight of maintaining complexity that adds nothing to the final experience.',
	'The nagging sense that there should be a more graceful way.',
];

const subtractionTabs = [
	{
		id: 'distillation',
		label: 'Distillation',
		title: 'Distillation Over Addition',
		body: "True craft lies not in accumulating features but in distilling to essence. Every line of code, every class, every component earns its place not through cleverness but through necessity. Like a master craftsman who knows which tool to reach for without thinking, you develop an intuition for what belongs and what doesn't.",
	},
	{
		id: 'rhythm',
		label: 'Rhythm',
		title: 'Rhythm Over Rules',
		body: "The best systems don't dictate—they dance. They establish a rhythm that your hands remember, patterns that feel inevitable once learned. Your workflow becomes fluid, your thinking becomes clear, your energy flows toward the work that matters.",
	},
	{
		id: 'foundation',
		label: 'Foundation',
		title: 'Foundation Over Fashion',
		body: 'While others chase trends, you build bedrock. You understand that true innovation comes from having a solid base to launch from, not from reinventing the ground beneath your feet with every project.',
	},
];
---

<Layout title="Inspired Layouts — Astro Starter">
	<SiteNav />

	<main id="main" tabindex="-1">
		<!-- Hero -->
		<header class="bg-brand pb-12 text-white md:pb-16 lg:pb-20">
			<div class="container-page space-y-10 pt-12 md:space-y-14 md:pt-16 lg:space-y-16 lg:pt-20">
				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-6 lg:col-span-9">
						<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-paper/80">The Steady Center</p>
						<h1>In turbulent waters, what matters most is what holds you steady</h1>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 items-end gap-8">
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-6 lg:col-span-6">
						<p class="text-body-lg text-paper/90">
							Every ship needs its mast—not because it's complex or clever, but because it's
							essential. It stands quietly at the center, bearing the fundamentals right.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-6 lg:flex lg:justify-end">
						<Button
							href="#problem"
							class="border-white text-white hover:bg-white/15"
							variant="secondary"
						>
							Begin with Purpose
							<ph-arrow-down slot="icon-right" weight="bold"></ph-arrow-down>
						</Button>
					</div>
				</div>

				<ImageSlider id="hero-gallery" images={heroSlides} autoplayMs={4000} />
			</div>
		</header>

		<!-- The Weight of Expectations -->
		<Section id="problem">
			<div class="container-page space-y-12 md:space-y-16">
				<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-center">
					<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Weight of Expectations</p>
					<h2>The burden of building without compass</h2>
				</div>

				<hr class="border-line" />

				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-4 lg:col-span-5">
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
							There's a particular exhaustion that comes from swimming against endless
							currents of complexity. You know the feeling—when every project feels like
							starting from scratch, when simple intentions become tangled in unnecessary
							complications, when you find yourself building the same foundations over and
							over.
						</p>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
							It's not about the tools themselves. It's about the mental load, the creative
							energy spent on mechanics instead of meaning.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-12 lg:col-span-6 lg:col-start-7">
						<div class="space-y-6">
							{
								burdenItems.map((item) => (
									<FeatureItem>
										<ph-minus slot="icon" class="text-xl" weight="bold" />
										{item}
									</FeatureItem>
								))
							}
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</Section>

		<!-- The Moment of Clarity -->
		<CoverSection src={`${cdn}8d_post6.webp`} alt="Soft light through fog">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-6 text-center">
				<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-paper/80">The Moment of Clarity</p>
				<h2>When noise fades, essence emerges</h2>
				<div class="space-y-4 text-body-lg text-paper/90">
					<p>
						But in those rare moments of clarity—perhaps late at night when the world is
						quiet, or in the pause before coffee kicks in—you glimpse something different.
						A way of working that feels like breathing. Where the structure serves the vision
						instead of constraining it.
					</p>
					<p>
						This isn't about revolutionary technology or groundbreaking innovation. It's
						about understanding what matters and letting everything else fall away. It's
						about finding your rhythm and building tools that move with it rather than
						against it.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</CoverSection>

		<!-- Split: portrait image + copy -->
		<Section theme="paper">
			<div class="container-page">
				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 items-center gap-8 lg:gap-12">
					<div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5">
						<MediaImage
							src={`${cdn}91_post4.webp`}
							alt="Figure in contemplation"
							ratio="inherit"
							class="aspect-[3/4] overflow-hidden rounded-lg"
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-4 md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7">
						<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Art of Subtraction</p>
						<h2>What you don't build is as important as what you do</h2>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
							True craft lies not in accumulating features but in distilling to essence.
							Every line of code, every class, every component earns its place not through
							cleverness but through necessity.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</Section>

		<!-- Tabs: Distillation / Rhythm / Foundation -->
		<Section>
			<div class="container-page space-y-10 md:space-y-14">
				<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-center">
					<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Art of Subtraction</p>
					<h2>What you don't build is as important as what you do</h2>
				</div>

				<Tabs
					id="subtraction-tabs"
					tabs={subtractionTabs.map((t) => ({ label: t.label, id: t.id }))}
				>
					<div slot="distillation" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-4 py-4 text-center md:py-8">
						<h3>{subtractionTabs[0].title}</h3>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">{subtractionTabs[0].body}</p>
					</div>
					<div slot="rhythm" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-4 py-4 text-center md:py-8">
						<h3>{subtractionTabs[1].title}</h3>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">{subtractionTabs[1].body}</p>
					</div>
					<div slot="foundation" class="mx-auto max-w-2xl space-y-4 py-4 text-center md:py-8">
						<h3>{subtractionTabs[2].title}</h3>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">{subtractionTabs[2].body}</p>
					</div>
				</Tabs>
			</div>
		</Section>

		<!-- The Quiet Confidence -->
		<Section theme="paper">
			<div class="container-page space-y-12 md:space-y-16">
				<div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
					<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Quiet Confidence</p>
					<h2>Those who build with purpose recognize each other</h2>
				</div>

				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-4 md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 lg:col-span-5 lg:col-start-8">
						<h3 class="text-h4">Community of Practice</h3>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
							There's a particular satisfaction that comes from working with tools that
							understand you. It's the difference between fighting your way through a project
							and flowing through it. Others notice—the clarity in your work, the speed of
							your delivery, the calm confidence in your process.
						</p>
						<p class="text-body text-ink-soft">
							The recognition comes not from the complexity you manage, but from the
							complexity you avoid.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-4 sm:gap-6">
					<div class="col-span-6 sm:col-span-3">
						<MediaImage src={`${cdn}a5_post9.webp`} alt="" ratio="4x3" class="rounded-lg" />
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-6 sm:col-span-3">
						<MediaImage src={`${cdn}a6_post8.webp`} alt="" ratio="4x3" class="rounded-lg" />
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-6 sm:col-span-3">
						<MediaImage src={`${cdn}a2_post10.webp`} alt="" ratio="4x3" class="rounded-lg" />
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-6 sm:col-span-3">
						<MediaImage src={`${cdn}a4_post7.webp`} alt="" ratio="4x3" class="rounded-lg" />
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</Section>

		<!-- The Expanding Horizon -->
		<Section>
			<div class="container-page">
				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 items-center gap-8 lg:gap-12">
					<div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-5">
						<MediaImage
							src={`${cdn}a7_post12.webp`}
							alt="Wide horizon"
							ratio="3x4"
							class="max-w-md"
						/>
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-4 md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7">
						<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Expanding Horizon</p>
						<h2>When the foundation is right, anything becomes possible</h2>
						<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
							With the mechanics handled, your mind is free to wander into more interesting
							territory. You're not debugging basic layouts or wrestling with inconsistent
							patterns. You're exploring ideas, refining experiences, solving problems that
							matter.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</Section>

		<!-- Scale Without Strain -->
		<CoverSection src={`${cdn}a9_post11.webp`} alt="Vast landscape">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
				<p class="text-eyebrow mb-6 uppercase tracking-wide text-paper/80">The Expanding Horizon</p>
				<blockquote class="text-h3 font-medium leading-snug md:text-h2">
					Scale Without Strain — Whether you're crafting something intimate and personal or
					building at enterprise scale, the same principles apply. Good bones support any
					structure. Clear thinking scales infinitely.
				</blockquote>
			</div>
		</CoverSection>

		<!-- The Practice -->
		<Section theme="paper">
			<div class="container-page space-y-12 md:space-y-16">
				<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-4 text-center">
					<p class="text-eyebrow uppercase tracking-wide text-brand">The Practice</p>
					<h2>Mastery lives in the daily discipline of choosing better</h2>
					<p class="text-body-lg text-ink-soft">
						This isn't about learning a new system—it's about remembering what you already
						know about good work. It's about choosing tools that align with your values,
						processes that support your thinking, and foundations that grow stronger with
						use.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8 lg:gap-12">
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-3 md:col-span-6">
						<h3 class="text-h4">The Daily Choice</h3>
						<p class="text-body text-ink-soft">
							Every project is an opportunity to build with intention. Every line of code is a
							chance to choose signal over noise. Every decision is a moment to ask: does this
							serve the vision or just fill space?
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="col-span-12 space-y-3 md:col-span-6">
						<h3 class="text-h4">The Compound Effect</h3>
						<p class="text-body text-ink-soft">
							Small improvements in your daily practice compound into dramatic differences in
							your work. Better tools lead to clearer thinking. Clearer thinking leads to
							better solutions. Better solutions lead to work that matters.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
					<MediaImage src={`${cdn}a8_post13.webp`} alt="" ratio="16x9" />
					<MediaImage src={`${cdn}8f_post3.webp`} alt="" ratio="16x9" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</Section>
	</main>

	<Footer />

	<script>
		import '@phosphor-icons/webcomponents/PhArrowDown';
		import '@phosphor-icons/webcomponents/PhMinus';
	</script>
</Layout>
